<title type="html"><![CDATA[Missing Lands (Ludum Dare)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=15854&amp;p=194210#p194210"><![CDATA[
Thought I'd give this one its own topic - did another Ludum Dare and made an NES game this time. Introducing...<br /><br /><span style="font-size: 200%; line-height: normal">Missing Lands</span><br /><br /><img src="http://i.imgur.com/3Ia5k5m.gif" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Missing Lands is a top-down action game featuring a frog in world with missing pieces. Your goal: to collect those pieces and restore your world.<br /><br />Rom download: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://cpprograms.net/devnull/world.nes">http://cpprograms.net/devnull/world.nes</a><!-- m --><br />Ludum Dare Page: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://ldjam.com/events/ludum-dare/38/missing-lands">https://ldjam.com/events/ludum-dare/38/missing-lands</a><!-- m --><br />Try it out here: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://cpprograms.net/classic-gaming/missing-lands/">http://cpprograms.net/classic-gaming/missing-lands/</a><!-- m --> <br /><span style="font-size: 85%; line-height: normal">(I probably don't have to tell you, but please download the rom instead of using the web-based emulator)</span><br /><br />For those not familiar with Ludum Dare, it's a contest where you build a game (including all assets) from scratch in 2 days.<br /><br />This isn't the most polished thing I've ever made, but I'd say it's definitely playable. Known quirks: <br />- Player's hitbox is too big. Just didn't think about it until it was too late. <br />- Sprite hitboxes are wonky for anything other than the player - causing them to sometimes overlap the rest of the world.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6316">cppchriscpp</a> â€” Mon Apr 24, 2017 4:53 pm</p><hr />
